gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Raptors 116, Grizzlies 111
gameRecap.excerpt: The Raptors defeated the Grizzlies, 116-111. Immanuel Quickley led the way for the Raptors with 26 points (5-8 3PT FG) and five assists, while Pascal Siakam added 24 points and seven rebounds in the victory. Ja Morant (28 points, eight rebounds, nine assists) and Jaren Jackson Jr. (24 points, four rebounds, four 3PM) combined for 52 points for the Grizzlies in the losing effort. The Raptors have won back-to-back games as they improve to 14-20 on the season, while the Grizzlies fall to 11-23.
